<div style="font-size:90%">
<br><br>

<b>June 3-4, 2011:  &nbsp;Etsuji Horii seminar
<br>
</b><br><br><br>

<a href="HoriiSeminarVenue.html">How to get there.</a><br><br>
 
Aikido Philippines (AP), Pilipinas Aikido Propagation Association (PAPA) and the Filipino Federation of Aikido (FFA) would like to invite all aikidoka to our mid-year seminar, to be taught by Etsuji Horii 7th dan. Horii entered Hombu Dojo in Tokyo in 1985, initially as an uchi-deshi, and eventually became an instructor at Hombu. Hori shihan moved back to his native Kobe in 1996 to establish his own Sanda Dojo. He remains very close to Doshu and Hombu and teaches many international seminars.<br><br>

Horii is known for his powerful technique. He says: "I have trained at Aikido World Headquarters of Aikikai Foundation for 10 years. I will devote all my strength for research and developement of Aikido as long as I live. I will look back at myself through the lessons, and find out the meaning of the words by the Founder Morihei Ueshiba, 'BU is Love.'"  Videos of his waza can be readily found on YouTube. Sanda Dojo can be found at http://www.lares.dti.ne.jp/%7Ehorii/index_e.html.<br><br>

<s>The Horii seminar will be held at the gym at the Golden Panda Dormtel, 447 E. Rodriguez Sr. Ave. corner Banawe, Quezon City. (Click here to view and/or download poster) (Click here to view and/or download vicinity map of seminar venue)<br><br>

There will be six classes: June 3, 5:00-6:30 pm/ 7:00-8:00 pm, June 4, 9:00 to 10:00 AM/ 10:30 to 12:00 nn/ 3:00 to 4:30 PM/ 5:00 to 6:30 PM. The seminar will be priced at P1,200 for all six sessions, and a mat fee of P200 per session. There is an P800 "early bird" offer for all those who pay before May 1, 2011.</s><br><br>

<i>(Text amended 2011 April 19)</i> The Horii seminar will be held at the gym at the International School Manila, University Parkway, Fort Bonifacio, Taguig City, 1634 Philippines. (<a href="Horii-Poster.jpg">Click here to view and/or download poster</a>) <a href="HoriiSeminarVenue.html">How to get there</a>.<br><br>

There will be six classes: June 3 (5:00-6:30 pm/ 7:00-8:30 pm); June 4 (8:30 to 10:00 AM/ 10:30 to 12:00 nn/ 3:00 to 4:30 PM/ 5:00 to 6:30 PM). The seminar will be priced at P1,200 for all six sessions, and a mat fee of P200 per session. There is an P800 "early bird" offer for all those who pay before May 15, 2011. <i>(Text amended April 19 ends.)</i><br><br>

For further inquiries, please contact us at 0918-4422777 or 0927-7971251 or 0915-3330055; or email us at Rommel Miel melmiel@yahoo.com, or Victor Ayes at victorwayes@hotmail.com or Raul Rodrigo at rvrodrigo@gmail.com. We look forward to training with you all in Horii's seminar this June.<br><br>

